cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY

The paper discusses the social network analysis of bibliometric data, which involves analyzing the relationships between papers, authors, institutes, countries, and journals. This could fall under several sub-categories, but the most relevant ones are likely to be cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these sub-categories deal with network analysis, bibliometrics, and information retrieval. Additionally, cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be relevant, as they deal with the development and impact of software and technology on society.
